# The CloudflareShard core Worker gates its entire /admin/* control surface on a
# single secret, ADMIN_TOKEN (see src/index.ts: env.ADMIN_TOKEN; the Worker
# returns 500 "ADMIN_TOKEN is not configured" if it's unset). It is NOT in
# wrangler [vars] because it is a secret, not public config.
#
# The Deploy to Cloudflare button reads this .env.example (dotenv format) and
# prompts the user to set it on the setup page. Set it to a STRONG random value
# — this token is the full admin credential for your cluster. Generate one with
# e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`. Anyone with it can init/reshard/drop.
#
# (This repo commits .env.example, not .dev.vars.example — see .gitignore's
# `!.env.example` negation; both are accepted by the Deploy button.)
ADMIN_TOKEN=replace-with-a-strong-random-secret
